    Azure Data Engineering End-To-End Project

    Click to edit text

    Section colours
    Duplicate section
    Delete the section

    Introduction

    Welcome to our comprehensive Azure Data Engineering Project, meticulously crafted to showcase my expertise in Azure services and data engineering. In this project, we orchestrate the extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) of data from diverse sources into Azure Data Lake Storage (ADLS) Gen 2. Leveraging Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, and Azure Synapse, this project embodies the principles of efficient data processing, advanced analytics, and scalable storage.

    Azure Data Lake Storage (ADLS) | Data Warehouse | Data Lake | 

    Star Schema | Snowflake Schema | ETL Processes


    Background: Total 4.5years of experience in IT industry and 3 years specializing in Azure Data Engineering, where I understand business and client requirements, design and build data pipelines to achieve objectives, and continuously monitor and troubleshoot to ensure optimal performance.

    • Source: OnPrem SQL Server

    • Source Format: Table

    • Sink: ADLS Gen 2

    • Sink File Format: Parquet

    • Incremental Loading: Utilizing watermarks to extract only new records.

    Data Transformation and Loading (Azure Databricks)

    • Raw Data Loading (Bronze Layer):

      • Mounting ADLS in Azure Databricks to read raw files.

      • Loading data into the Bronze layer as Delta tables.

      • Preserving raw data for traceability and historical analysis.

    • Data Transformation (Silver Layer):

      • Cleaning data by addressing data type issues, handling null values, and checking for duplicates.

      • Saving the transformed data into the Silver layer in ADLS as Delta tables.


    Click to edit text

    Section colours

    Data Analysis and Synapse Integration

    • Star Schema Creation:

      • In Azure Databricks:

        • Developed a Gold Notebook for advanced data analysis.

        • Loaded data from the Silver layer in ADLS.

        • Formulated a star schema for efficient analytical queries.

        • Conducted various analyses and exploratory data analysis (EDA) within Databricks.

      • In Azure Synapse Analytics:

        • Created external tables pointing to Delta tables in the Silver layer.

        • Built a star schema within Azure Synapse for additional analytical capabilities.

        • Enabled seamless integration for advanced analytics within Synapse Studio.

    Advanced Features

    • External Tables and Merge Operations:

      • External tables in the Silver layer provide efficient data access.

      • Leveraging merge operations in Databricks to insert only new records.

    • COPY INTO Command for File Processing:

      • Implementing the COPY INTO command to process files only once in Databricks.

      • Enhancing performance by avoiding redundant file processing.

    Master Pipeline and CI/CD Integration

    • Master Pipeline in Azure Data Factory:

      • Centralized control for end-to-end data workflows.

      • Orchestrating data extraction, transformation, and loading.

    • Version Control and CI/CD with Git and Azure DevOps:

      • Using Git for version control, enabling collaborative development.

      • Implementing continuous integration and deployment with Azure DevOps for reliable deployments.

    Customer Dataset Enhancement

    • Type 2 Slowly Changing Dimension (SCD):

      • Implementing Type 2 SCD for the customer dataset.

      • Capturing historical changes and enabling historical analysis.

    Benefits

    • Efficiency: Streamlined ETL processes, including incremental loading, enhance the efficiency of data workflows.

    • Automation: The master pipeline in Azure Data Factory, coupled with CI/CD pipelines in Azure DevOps, automates end-to-end processes, ensuring consistent and reliable deployment.

    • Flexibility: Git-based version control allows for collaborative development, tracks changes over time, and ensures project flexibility.

    • Scalability: Leveraging Azure services facilitates scalable data processing, accommodating growing datasets and future expansion.

    • Reliability: Continuous Integration and Deployment (CI/CD) pipelines implemented through Azure DevOps ensure reliable and error-free deployment to production environments.

    • Historical Analysis: The implementation of Type 2 Slowly Changing Dimension (SCD) enables historical analysis of changes in the customer dataset over time.

    • Advanced Analytics: Star schema analyses conducted in both Azure Databricks and Synapse Analytics empower users with advanced analytical capabilities for deeper insights.


    Conclusion

    Our Azure Data Engineering Project seamlessly integrates data from diverse sources, transforming it into a unified, efficient, and analytically rich format. By combining the power of Azure services and advanced ETL techniques, we ensure a scalable, reliable, and future-proof data processing solution. The addition of star schema analyses in both Azure Databricks and Synapse Analytics exemplifies our commitment to providing insightful and actionable data for advanced analytics
